article.headline: Dartmouth 34, Yale 14
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Alex Park was 15-of-27 passing for 204 yards and a touchdown to lead Dartmouth to a 34-14 victory against Yale on Saturday, ending a 10-game losing streak against the Bulldogs. Yale had won the past five at home by a combined score of 171-34, with the past three decided by a margin of at least 30 points Dartmouth (3-1, 1-1 Ivy League) trailed 14-13 at the half but shut out Yale (1-3, 0-2) in the second half and scored 14 fourth-quarter points to seal the victory. Yale went for it on fourth down four times in the second half, including at Dartmouth's 6- and 11-yard lines, but turned the ball over on downs all four times. Dominick Pierre ran for 91 yards and a touchdown for the Big Green, and Brian Grove scored two rushing touchdowns. The Bulldogs' Eric Williams threw for 181 yards and a touchdown.
